    "narrative": "The Austin Waves roster is headlined today by **Kyle Tucker** (76.51), whose elite hitting environment makes him our strongest start against Colin Rea. With wind blowing out providing an extra 5% boost to his already strong projection, he is the clear centerpiece of the lineup. Joining him in the top tier are **Jackson Merrill** (70.76) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.45). **Jackson Merrill** maintains a strong score despite the 36% rain risk, as the dynamic platoon advantage against Zac Gallen elevates his floor, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a 7% boost in a favorable matchup against Joey Cantillo. We are also banking on **Josh Jung** (59.81) and **Miguel Vargas** (59.07) to stabilize the middle order, with both benefiting significantly from favorable matchups against starters with xERAs near or above 4.60.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (48.31), who narrowly missed the starting cut. While his raw base projection remains respectable, the optimizer favored the defensive versatility and platoon matchups of our bottom-of-the-order options like **Andy Pages** (60.94), who remains a start due to the park-wide wind benefit and solid matchup against Colin Rea. We are exercising caution with **Gunnar Henderson** (54.00), whose high-ceiling park factors are currently being stifled by an elite matchup against Garrett Crochet. Investors should monitor the official lineup cards for **Drake Baldwin**, **Liam Hicks**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Josh Jung**, **Dominic Smith**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Heliot Ramos**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** closely, as the \"Lineup Pending\" status on several key pieces could shift these scores once batting orders are confirmed.",
